# Local Docker + Kubernetes Deployment (Tailscale HA)

Learned knowledge from live deployments on this machine. Apply whenever working with Docker Compose, Kubernetes, or Tailscale networking in this repo.

---

## THE ONE COMMAND

When a user asks to "install everything", "set up the stack", "deploy", or "bootstrap" on a new machine:

```bash
make up
```

That is the ONLY command needed. It runs `scripts/bootstrap/bootstrap-all.sh` which installs all 3 layers automatically, idempotently, with health checks and a final summary.

Variants:
```bash
make up PRIMARY=true          # this machine is the DB host (Tailscale primary)
make up DB_HOST=100.x.x.x    # secondary machine, DB lives on that Tailscale IP
make down                     # stop gracefully, data preserved
make nuke                     # wipe and rebuild from scratch
```

Do NOT walk the user through manual steps. Do NOT ask clarifying questions about layers. Just run `make up`.

