## One-Command Flows

### First machine (primary — hosts postgres/redis for the whole Tailscale cluster)
```bash
make docker-up && make k8s-install-primary
```

### Every additional machine (secondary — on Tailscale)
```bash
make docker-up && bash scripts/bootstrap/install-k8s.sh --db-host 100.79.214.33
```
Replace `100.79.214.33` with the primary machine's Tailscale IP.

### Clean reinstall (any machine, keeps Docker volumes)
```bash
make k8s-reinstall
```

### Full nuclear reset (wipes all data)
```bash
make k8s-uninstall && make docker-down
bash scripts/seed.sh --reset
make docker-up && make k8s-install
```

