## Scripts Reference

| Script | When | What It Does |
|--------|------|--------------|
| `scripts/backup.sh` | Before ANY infra change | DB dump + volume tarballs → `~/medinovai-backups/medinovai-Deploy/` |
| `scripts/restore.sh --from-latest` | After data loss | Stop stack → restore DB → restart |
| `scripts/seed.sh` | New machine / fresh env | Start infra → run migrations → start all services |
| `scripts/seed.sh --reset` | Nuclear reset | Wipe all volumes → rebuild from scratch |
| `scripts/bootstrap/tailscale-config.sh --primary` | First run on primary | Write `.env.tailscale` + `configmap-env-local.yaml` |
| `scripts/bootstrap/tailscale-config.sh --db-host <ip>` | First run on secondary | Same, pointing at primary's Tailscale IP |
| `scripts/bootstrap/install-k8s.sh` | Install / update K8s | Tailscale config → infra up → apply manifests → wait healthy |
| `scripts/bootstrap/install-k8s.sh --primary` | Primary machine | Same + registers this machine as DB host |
| `scripts/bootstrap/uninstall-k8s.sh` | Remove K8s only | Delete `medinovai-*` namespaces + resources (keeps Docker) |
| `scripts/bootstrap/uninstall-k8s.sh --also-infra` | Remove everything | Uninstall K8s + stop Docker Compose |
| `scripts/bootstrap/instantiate-docker.sh` | Full greenfield Docker | 8-step bootstrap with pre/post-deploy backup checkpoints |

