## 200-Repo Bulk Deployment

The full MedinovAI system consists of ~200 repositories in `myonsite-healthcare` GitHub org.
They are all deployed to Docker Desktop Kubernetes via the smart deploy engine.

### Clone All 200 Repos

```bash
# Requires gh CLI authenticated to myonsite-healthcare org
gh repo list myonsite-healthcare --limit 200 --json name,sshUrl \
  --jq '.[] | "git clone " + .sshUrl + " ~/medinovai-all-repos/" + .name' \
  > /tmp/clone_all.sh
bash /tmp/clone_all.sh
```

### Deploy Engine

Located at `scripts/deploy-all-repos.py`. Log output → `logs/deploy-history.json`.

```bash
# See plan without making changes
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py --dry-run

# Fix Dockerfiles only (safe, no K8s changes)
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py --fix-only

# Deploy tier 1 (registry must come first)
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py --tier 1

# Deploy everything
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py

# Deploy a single repo
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py --repo medinovai-registry

# Check current K8s pod health summary
python3 scripts/deploy-all-repos.py --status
```

### Tier Deployment Order

| Tier | Repos | Must be healthy before next tier |
|------|-------|----------------------------------|
| 1 | `medinovai-registry` | Yes |
| 2 | `medinovai-data-services`, `medinovai-secrets-manager-bridge`, `medinovai-universal-sign-on`, `medinovai-role-based-permissions`, `medinovai-real-time-stream-bus`, `medinovai-saes` | Yes |
| 3 | `medinovai-aifactory`, `medinovai-healthLLM`, `medinovai-lis`, `medinovai-Cortex` | Yes |
| 4+ | All remaining 190+ repos | N/A |

### imagePullPolicy: Never Mandate

All 200-repo services use locally-built Docker images. Every K8s manifest MUST include:
```yaml
imagePullPolicy: Never
```
Without it, K8s will attempt Docker Hub pull → `ErrImagePull` on a local image.

### REGISTRY_URL Injection

Every K8s deployment must include:
```yaml
env:
- name: REGISTRY_URL
  value: "http://medinovai-registry.medinovai:8000"
```

