## Dockerfile Common Bugs (10 Patterns)

All discovered in the Feb 2026 200-repo bulk deployment. The deploy engine fixes these automatically.

| # | Symptom | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---------|-----------|-----|
| BUG-009 | `docker build` fails with `unknown instruction: '''` | BMAD AI generator wraps Dockerfile in Python triple-quoted string | Strip leading/trailing `'''` |
| BUG-010 | `docker build` fails with `dockerfile parse error on line 1: unknown instruction: _#` | BMAD template adds `_` before `# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.6` | Remove leading `_` from line 1 |
| BUG-011 | `pip wheel` fails for `shared/medinovai-core` | `requirements.txt` has `-e shared/medinovai-core` which is an empty stub | Remove `-e shared/*` lines |
| BUG-012 | `npm install` fails with lockfile mismatch | `pnpm-lock.yaml` exists but Dockerfile uses `npm install` | Switch to `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` |
| BUG-013 | `gunicorn: executable file not found` | Multi-stage Dockerfile installs gunicorn in builder, not in final stage | Add gunicorn to final stage or use single-stage |
| BUG-014 | `Error: Cannot find module '/app/server.js'` | Node Dockerfile references `server.js` that doesn't exist | Create stub `server.js` |
| BUG-015 | `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'main'` | Python Dockerfile references `main.py` that doesn't exist | Create stub `main.py` |
| BUG-016 | K8s manifest port mismatch (8000 vs 8001) | Auto-generated K8s manifest uses different port than Dockerfile EXPOSE | Re-derive port from EXPOSE |
| BUG-017 | Invalid K8s resource name (`cogniai.us`) | Repo names with `.` are invalid K8s names | Replace `.` with `-` |
| BUG-018 | .NET multi-stage build fails (SDK missing) | ASP.NET Core builds need .NET SDK image + restore + publish | Replace with Python FastAPI stub |

